Blocks.Text: The political life of Aristoble Cooked more and more
like a masquerade of business interests in dis-
quise which, far from attracting the allegiance
of free men everywhere, could only repel them.
Then what of the cultural life ? Did this per-
haps nurture a genuinely civilizing impulse
which might in time become social fact
and counteract the obsersion with economics
which had groten up during the Monn's
